<item>
            <title>[JDK-8305711] Arm: C2 always enters slowpath for monitorexit</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8305711</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Due to a small bug in the C2 implementation of monitorexit for stacklocked locks, we always enter slow path.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
AFAICS This is a day zero bug of the arm port and got introduced with JEP 297: &amp;quot;Unified arm32/arm64 Port&amp;quot;. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
It has a significant effect on locking performance, but its effect had been hidden until JDK15 by biased locking. Biased locking removal made the bug appearant.</description>
